<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1640,1981]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1641,1665]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[458,573,1640,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Weissflogia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[458,573,1640,1664]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means pubescent, bringing attention to the setae on the head and elytra that are longer and denser than those of the congener 
<taxonomicName box="[700,892,1676,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Weissflogia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhopalogaster">
<emphasis box="[700,721,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">W</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[735,892,1676,1700]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">rhopalogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1640,1981]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,1710,1735]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
Almost uniformly reddish brown. Head (
<figureCitation box="[831,970,1711,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 – 81" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1662]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 74 – 81. Weissflogia pubescens sp. nov. (76 – 81, SEM photographs). 74, Habitus, dorsal view; 75, ditto, lateral view; 76, head, pronotum and anterior part of elytra, lateral view; 77, head, dorsal view; 78, pronotum, dorsal view; 79, abdominal tergites III – VI, dorsal view; 80, abdomen, lateral view; 81, abdominal sternite III – V, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201595/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number box="[899,970,1711,1735]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="75.5" valueMax="77.0" valueMin="74.0">74–77</number>
</figureCitation>
) sparsely covered with setae except for between eyes. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[446,529,1746,1770]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 – 81" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1662]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 74 – 81. Weissflogia pubescens sp. nov. (76 – 81, SEM photographs). 74, Habitus, dorsal view; 75, ditto, lateral view; 76, head, pronotum and anterior part of elytra, lateral view; 77, head, dorsal view; 78, pronotum, dorsal view; 79, abdominal tergites III – VI, dorsal view; 80, abdomen, lateral view; 81, abdominal sternite III – V, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201595/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[500,529,1746,1770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="78.0">78</number>
</figureCitation>
) with ratio length /width = 
<number box="[838,954,1746,1770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.42" valueMax="1.44" valueMin="1.4">1.40–1.44</number>
, with a row of 
<number box="[1130,1144,1746,1770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="5.0">5</number>
or 
<number box="[1185,1199,1746,1770]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="6.0">6</number>
setae along midline, 
<number box="[151,221,1781,1805]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14</number>
small setae laterally and 
<number box="[508,522,1781,1805]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number box="[560,574,1781,1805]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
setae posteriorly. Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[863,945,1781,1805]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 – 81" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1662]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 74 – 81. Weissflogia pubescens sp. nov. (76 – 81, SEM photographs). 74, Habitus, dorsal view; 75, ditto, lateral view; 76, head, pronotum and anterior part of elytra, lateral view; 77, head, dorsal view; 78, pronotum, dorsal view; 79, abdominal tergites III – VI, dorsal view; 80, abdomen, lateral view; 81, abdominal sternite III – V, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201595/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[916,945,1781,1805]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="78.0">78</number>
</figureCitation>
) sparsely covered with minute setae except for medial area of each elytron, with a large seta near base of scutellum. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1243,1816,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 – 81" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1683,1706]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1662]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 74 – 81. Weissflogia pubescens sp. nov. (76 – 81, SEM photographs). 74, Habitus, dorsal view; 75, ditto, lateral view; 76, head, pronotum and anterior part of elytra, lateral view; 77, head, dorsal view; 78, pronotum, dorsal view; 79, abdominal tergites III – VI, dorsal view; 80, abdomen, lateral view; 81, abdominal sternite III – V, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201595/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number box="[1172,1243,1816,1840]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="80.0" valueMax="81.0" valueMin="79.0">79–81</number>
</figureCitation>
) with sternite III widest around apical 
<number box="[392,403,1851,1875]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[415,430,1851,1875]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
; paratergites III–V slightly matte; numbers of macrosetae from tergite II–VIII: 1, 1, 0, 2, 2, 6. Male: median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[584,721,1887,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 82 – 87" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[250,1337,181,1511]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[248,1341,177,1512]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 82 – 87. Weissflogia spp. 82 – 84, W. pubescens sp. nov.; 85 – 87, W. rhopalogaster (82, 85, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 83, 86, ditto, ventral view; 84, 87, spermatheca; 82, 83, holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201596/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 82, 83</figureCitation>
) with apical lobe dilated apically, base of parameral side shallowly emarginate in lateral view; apex of apical lobe thin laterally in parameral view. Female: spermatheca (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 82 – 87" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[250,1337,181,1511]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[248,1341,177,1512]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 82 – 87. Weissflogia spp. 82 – 84, W. pubescens sp. nov.; 85 – 87, W. rhopalogaster (82, 85, median lobe of aedeagus, lateral view; 83, 86, ditto, ventral view; 84, 87, spermatheca; 82, 83, holotype)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/201596/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1957,1981]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
) with basal part short.
</paragraph>
